# Swift Style

- No force unwrap (`!`); use optional binding, `guard let`
- Prefer struct over class for value types
- Enum with associated values for state/result
- Naming: ViewModels `{Screen}ViewModel`, Services `{Entity}Service`, DTOs `{Entity}Dto`
- Swift 6 concurrency: @MainActor for UI, Sendable where needed
- No "I" prefix on protocols
